if git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACMR | grep -qx 'e2e/pairings-snapshots.ts'; then
  if [ "$ALLOW_SNAPSHOT_REGEN" != "1" ]; then
    cat >&2 <<'EOF'
✗ Refusing to commit changes to e2e/pairings-snapshots.ts

This file is the golden-master pairing snapshot. It locks the expected
board pairings + final standings for every pairing-algorithm scenario.
A drift here is almost always a regression in the pairing engine, not
something you "fix" by regenerating the snapshot.

History note: the previous version was captured against the old
stateless Java REST API (which had a lotNr bug). The frontend port
deliberately diverged to match Swing's correct stateful behavior. Do
not regenerate just because tests fail — first verify the pairing
output is actually correct.

If you genuinely intend to regenerate (e.g. deliberate engine change,
verified against Swing reference output):

  ALLOW_SNAPSHOT_REGEN=1 git commit ...
EOF
    exit 1
  fi
fi

pnpm exec lint-staged

FILES=$(git diff --cached --name-only --diff-filter=ACMR)
[ -n "$FILES" ] && pnpm exec secretlint --maskSecrets $FILES

pnpm exec knip --no-config-hints
pnpm exec jscpd src/
pnpm exec tsc -b
